# ERP Record Workspace Form Standard

**Status:** IMPLEMENTED — ERP GLOBAL UI.4C (2026-06-14)  
**Activate alwaysApply:** After first module is converted (ERP GLOBAL UI.4D — Party Master pilot)  
**Components:** `src/components/workspace/erp-record-workspace-form.tsx` and siblings

---

## Rule 1 — When to use ERPRecordWorkspaceForm vs ERPDrawerForm

Use `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm` for any entity meeting 2+ of these criteria:

- 5 or more navigation sections/tabs
- Has child tables (contacts, addresses, bank details, documents, etc.)
- Has audit/notes/compliance tabs
- Is a "long-lived entity" (not a quick setup value)
- Users frequently switch context while editing

```
REQUIRES ERPRecordWorkspaceForm (convert in UI.4D+):
✓ Party Master (12 tabs, 8+ child tables)
✓ Customers (after Party Master)
✓ Future: Employee profile
✓ Future: Fleet asset / equipment
✓ Future: Purchase Order / Invoice
✓ Future: Job Card / Workshop order
✓ Future: Project
✓ Future: DMS document record

KEEP ERPDrawerForm:
✓ Organizations, Branches (2–3 fields)
✓ Roles, Permissions (simple forms)
✓ Geography, Finance Basics, UOM, Lookups (≤ 5 fields)
✓ Numbering Rules, Users, Admin forms
```

---

## Rule 2 — ERPRecordWorkspaceForm anatomy

Every record workspace form must follow this layout:

```
ERPRecordWorkspaceForm
  ├── ERPRecordHeader              (shrink-0, always visible)
  │    ├── Record code badge       (font-mono, auto-generated)
  │    ├── Display name + subtitle
  │    ├── Status badge
  │    ├── Mode badge (Add / Editing / View)
  │    ├── Type badges
  │    ├── Dirty indicator (amber dot + "Unsaved")
  │    └── Close (X) button → calls onRequestClose
  ├── Content zone                 (flex-1, inert-able for child dialogs)
  │    ├── ERPRecordSectionNav     (240px desktop / horizontal mobile)
  │    └── ScrollArea body         (flex-1, overflow-auto)
  │         └── ERPRecordSection panels (lazyMount for child-table sections)
  └── ERPRecordFormFooter          (shrink-0, always visible)
       ├── Add/Edit: Cancel · Save · Save & Close
       └── View:     Close
```

