## Rule 4 — Dirty state

Every record workspace form MUST wire dirty state:

```tsx
// In the record form component:
const { isDirty, resetDirty } = useFormDirty({ formId, enabled: mode !== "view" });
const { requestClose, showUnsavedDialog, confirmDiscard, cancelDiscard } =
  useRecordWorkspaceForm({ formId, mode, isDirty, onClose: () => /* navigate away */ });

<ERPRecordWorkspaceForm
  isDirty={isDirty}
  onRequestClose={requestClose}
  ...
/>
```

- `useRecordWorkspaceForm` calls `useWorkspaceTabDirty` internally — no manual call needed.
- Tab dirty dot appears automatically when `isDirty = true`.
- Save MUST call `resetDirty()` after successful save.
- Do NOT persist unsaved form field values to localStorage or workspace state.

---

## Rule 5 — Safe close

```
Close button / Cancel / X
  └── calls onRequestClose → useRecordWorkspaceForm().requestClose
        ├── Inside WorkspaceProvider: workspace.closeTab(activeTabId)
        │     └── WorkspaceProvider (4B) handles dirty dialog
        └── Outside WorkspaceProvider: internal UnsavedChangesDialog fallback
```

Avoid double dialogs: do NOT add a separate dirty check in the form if already using `useRecordWorkspaceForm` + WorkspaceProvider.

---

## Rule 6 — Child dialogs

Child form dialogs inside a record form MUST use `ERPChildDialogForm`.

When a child dialog opens, pass `isChildDialogOpen={true}` to `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm`:

```tsx
<ERPRecordWorkspaceForm
  isChildDialogOpen={childDialogOpen}
  ...
>
  {/* child dialog portals to body — escapes inert zone */}
  <ERPChildDialogForm open={childDialogOpen} ... />
```

The inert wrapper covers: section nav + body + footer.  
It does NOT cover: header, workspace tab bar, sidebar.

---

## Rule 7 — Section panels

Use `ERPRecordSection` from `erp-record-workspace-form.tsx`:

```tsx
<ERPRecordSection id="contacts" activeId={activeSection} lazyMount>
  <ContactsContent />
</ERPRecordSection>
```

lazyMount rule (same as ERPDrawerSection):
- Set `lazyMount` on sections whose fields are NOT included in parent FormData.
- Display-only sections and child-CRUD sections are safe candidates.

---

## Rule 8 — Section nav

Pass a `sections` array to `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm`:

```tsx
const sections: ERPRecordSection[] = [
  { id: "basic", label: "Basic Information", icon: <Building2 className="h-3.5 w-3.5" /> },
  { id: "contacts", label: "Contacts", badge: contactCount, lazyMount: true },
  { id: "audit", label: "Audit", disabled: mode === "add" },
];
```

Do NOT hardcode section IDs — define them as a `const` at the module level.

---

## Rule 9 — Mode management

```
mode="add"   → all sections enabled, Cancel = discard new record, Save = create
mode="edit"  → all sections enabled, Cancel = discard edits, Save = update
mode="view"  → read-only, Close button only, no dirty tracking
```

Switching from view → edit should NOT create a new workspace tab. Update the tab's `formMode` via `RENAME_TAB` or `workspaceStore` dispatch.

---

## Rule 10 — Naming

Workspace record tabs:
- Title: Entity display name ("ABC Contracting LLC") or "New [EntityType]"
- Subtitle: Record code when available ("PTY-000001")
- tabKind: "record"
- entityType: e.g. "party", "customer", "vendor"
- entityId: DB primary key (when editing existing record)

After first save of a new record:
- Call `dispatch({ type: "RENAME_TAB", tabId, title: displayName, subtitle: recordCode })`.

---

## Rule 11 — Forbidden patterns

```
✗ Do NOT use Sheet/ERPDrawerForm for entities listed in Rule 1
✗ Do NOT store unsaved form values in workspace or localStorage
✗ Do NOT block workspace tab bar from child dialogs
✗ Do NOT duplicate dirty-close dialogs
✗ Do NOT use ERPRecordWorkspaceForm for simple admin forms
✗ Do NOT skip calling resetDirty() after successful save
```

