## Rule 13 — Section state and scroll state are mandatory (UI.4E)

Every `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm` implementation **must** use `useWorkspaceSectionState` to persist the active section across workspace tab switches.

```ts
import { useWorkspaceSectionState } from "@/hooks/use-workspace-section-state";

// Existing record:
const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useWorkspaceSectionState({
  key: "active-section",
  initialSection: "basic",
  scope: "record",
  recordType: "party",   // change per entity
  recordId: entity.id,
});

// New/unsaved record:
const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useWorkspaceSectionState({
  key: "active-section",
  initialSection: "basic",
  scope: "tab",
  identifier: activeTab?.id ?? "new",
});
```

Scroll state via `useWorkspaceScrollState` + the `bodyScrollRef` prop of `ERPRecordWorkspaceForm` is strongly recommended.

---

## Rule 14 — Do not persist sensitive form field values

`useWorkspaceSectionState` only persists the active section ID (a string).  
`useWorkspaceScrollState` only persists scroll coordinates (numbers).

Never cache form field values, PII, financial identifiers, or unsaved business data.  
See `docs/standards/ERP_GLOBAL_WORKSPACE_OPEN_ELEMENT_CACHE_STANDARD.md`.

---

## Rule 15 — Legacy `*-form-dialog.tsx` files are deleted (CLEANUP.2)

All pre-workspace `*-form-dialog.tsx` files for main Add/Edit/View CRUD operations
were removed in **ERP GLOBAL CLEANUP.2** (2026-06-14). 21 files deleted.

```
✗ Do NOT create new *-form-dialog.tsx files for main CRUD forms.
✗ Do NOT import or resurrect deleted legacy form-dialog components.
✓ Main Add/Edit/View → ERPRecordWorkspaceForm (workspace record tab)
✓ Child Add/Edit → ERPChildDialogForm (blocking modal)
```

Any new CRUD form must follow the workspace pattern from day one.
